verbose_text: Growth factors have vital roles in this process, for example, it seems that overexpression of TGFbeta1 may mediate fibrosis in wound while bFGF may promote scarless healing and reduce scarring in this process (Akita, Akino, & Hirano, 2013; Liu et al., 2016; Shah, Foreman, & Ferguson, 1995; Shi et al., 2013; Song, Bian, Lai, Chen, & Zhao, 2011; Wang et al., 2017).
